    "Our update process follows the form:x t+1 = P ϵ ℓ∞(δ t) x t ± αsign∇ x t J x t,(18)where we apply plus for maximization and minus for minimization, and P ϵ ℓ∞(δ t) (•) will apply the projection on δ t in the ϵ-ball of ℓ ∞ norm, α is a hyperparameter to adjust the learning rate during the optimization.Algorithm 1 presents the complete optimization procedure of our Posterior Collapse Attack.",
    "The algorithm takes a clean image x and the VAE encoder E as inputs, along with standard adversarial attack parameters: perturbation budget ϵ, step size α, and number of iterations T. Two method-specific parameters control the attack behavior: the variance parameter v and the objective type obj ∈ {+, -}.The optimization follows an iterative gradient-based approach.",
    "At each iteration t, we:1) Extract the mean µ t and variance σ t from the encoder's output (Line 3).",
    "2) Compute the loss L KL (in Equation 12) between the posterior distribution q(z|x t-1) and target distribution p * (z) = N (0, vI) (Line 5).",
    "3) Calculate the gradient with respect to the input image (Line 7)."
